Use Tailwind CSS for styling with utility-first approach.

Component styling patterns:

Use Tailwind utility classes directly in JSX

For complex styles, use CSS-in-JS with Tailwind's @apply directive

Create reusable component variants using class-variance-authority (cva)

Use Tailwind's design tokens (colors, spacing, typography) consistently

Keep custom CSS minimal - prefer Tailwind utilities

Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)

Leverage Tailwind's dark mode with dark: prefix

Component structure:
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority"

const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground hover:bg-destructive/90",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 rounded-md px-3",
        lg: "h-11 rounded-md px-8",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
)
```